replies.body:
Alright, but it isn't a problem that only mages have at all.
If you look at Assasins class(AD), you will notice that the case isn't very different.
The build usually is:
{{item:3147}} {{item:3142}} {{item:3071}} {{item:3035}}  {{item:3814}}  / {{item:3026}}  {{item:3047}} / {{item:3111}} 

And only 3 of those items are really assasins items, plus they suffer from the fact that they can be abused by marksmen and for that reason they have been nerfed over and over again.
If that wasn't bad, Assasins in order to become actual Assasins, are balanced around {{item:3147}} damage proc for god knows what reason.

You could tell me we also have this items:
{{item:3139}} {{item:3156}} 
But that items are flat out garbage, and if you picked an Assasin against a team with a lot of CC, you're going to have a big bad time even if you build {{item:3139}} , for example. In the case of Maw, it's just bad. Some players may abuse the {{item:3155}} in the laning phase though, but at the cost of a {{item:3134}} , wich provides much more raw damage and one shot potencial.

Look, I may have looked angry in my comment, but isn't because of you. I have a big issue with the boards because they always favour mages over anything, and I've seen a lot of ridiculous suggestions being upvoted without making any sense.

The other topic you talked about was the difference between mages.
I don't think they're all equal at all, in fact I think the mages have a vast variety on their own:

Burst mages: {{champion:63}} {{champion:134}} ;

Utility / Poke / Burst: {{champion:61}} (Yes, I hate her. She's a lane bully that perma pokes you, has a shield to win trades and offers a huge team fight potencial with her ulti that can one shot squishy's that have no MR items (and if she's not too much behind));

Poke: {{champion:101}} {{champion:161}} {{champion:115}} 
Especially this guy {{champion:101}}  that is insanely strong at the moment, and in my opinion someone that requires so much skill to play beind so good proves that something is wrong;

CC Machines / Control mages: {{champion:127}} {{champion:90}} {{champion:34}} {{champion:163}} (not sure about Taliyah

DPS: {{champion:69}} {{champion:13}} 

Divers: {{champion:8}}

And there are many others.
So far, in my opinion, they have a huge diversity and each one of them can do different things.

> [{quoted}](name=Skorch,realm=NA,application-id=3ErqAdtq,discussion-id=Kf5EFkbh,comment-id=000a0000,timestamp=2018-01-11T02:01:38.725+0000)
>
> People are upset fighters (Top lane carries) arent viable.

[citation needed]

fighters are dominating top lane right now only three tanks of the entire cast are performing consistent up there -- {{champion:54}} {{champion:57}} {{champion:14}} 

Meanwhile more and more kleptomancy/comet  abusing divers, juggernauts, and skirmishers are destroying tanks throughout laning while being levels ahead of them for later teamfights. {{champion:10}} {{champion:41}} {{champion:75}} {{champion:24}} {{champion:240}} {{champion:420}} {{champion:164}} {{champion:2}} {{champion:80}} {{champion:92}} {{champion:107}} {{champion:126}} {{champion:114}} {{champion:83}} {{champion:266}} {{champion:122}} {{champion:62}} 

All in the upper 50% of toplaners -- 17 of the top 27 

While 7 of the 10 tanks played top have among the worst winrates in that role: {{champion:78}} {{champion:516}} {{champion:3}} {{champion:111}} {{champion:223}} {{champion:98}} {{champion:20}} 

Even being generous with the term tank to include {{champion:27}} {{champion:31}}, it's still only 4 out of 12 doing well.

Fighters now not only shit on tanks thoughout the early game denying them cs for risk of the tank dying fucking instantly before they get their 3 items, but also end up setting the tanks so far behind they can't afford items needed for teamfights, while fighters enjoy the luxury of clearing a wave in a single ability cast and obliterating towers that are left alone for more than 3 seconds.
